01:07:18,576 --> 01:07:20,369
What gave you that impression?

787
01:07:21,538 --> 01:07:23,163
Aren't me hands cold?

788
01:07:23,748 --> 01:07:25,374
I quite like it.

789
01:07:35,468 --> 01:07:37,553
Just 'cause I like ballet

790
01:07:37,887 --> 01:07:40,222
doesn't mean I'm a poof, you know?

791
01:07:42,559 --> 01:07:45,144
(STUTTERING)
You won't tell anyone, will you?

792
01:07:49,733 --> 01:07:51,358
Come on.

793
01:08:04,831 --> 01:08:07,082
It's fucking freezing in here.

794
01:08:07,709 --> 01:08:09,543
Here.

795
01:08:09,627 --> 01:08:12,588
-What's this?
-Just put it on.

796
01:08:12,672 --> 01:08:14,006
A tutu.

797
01:08:14,132 --> 01:08:16,300
(ALL CHATTERING)

798
01:08:20,847 --> 01:08:22,848
George. George.
There's somebody in the club.

799
01:08:22,974 --> 01:08:25,434
...this kangaroo,
he's walking away over it, right?

800
01:08:25,518 --> 01:08:28,312
And he's called Norman. (LAUGHS)

801
01:08:28,396 --> 01:08:31,940
And then round the corner came this wallaby.

802
01:08:42,869 --> 01:08:44,995
Plié, first.

803
01:08:45,497 --> 01:08:46,997
What's a plié?

804
01:08:47,081 --> 01:08:48,624
It's French.

805
01:08:48,708 --> 01:08:49,917
Why's it French?

806
01:08:50,001 --> 01:08:53,545
I don't know. Second. Like a princess.

807
01:09:00,428 --> 01:09:02,721
Second, and down.

808
01:09:03,848 --> 01:09:07,351
And first. Carry on. Fifth.

809
01:09:09,145 --> 01:09:12,105
Shoulders down, long neck.

810
01:09:12,190 --> 01:09:13,482
How do I look?

811
01:09:13,566 --> 01:09:14,650
Shut up, you poof.

812
01:09:14,734 --> 01:09:15,776
Fuck off!

813
01:09:17,070 --> 01:09:19,530
Second, and down.

814
01:09:21,074 --> 01:09:22,991
And first.

815
01:09:23,701 --> 01:09:26,787
Fifth. Second.

816
01:09:27,747 --> 01:09:28,831
Down.

817
01:09:29,582 --> 01:09:32,084
First. Fifth.

818
01:09:33,878 --> 01:09:35,879
Jackie.

819
01:09:35,964 --> 01:09:38,590
Jackie, man. Here.

820
01:09:41,219 --> 01:09:43,387
Give us your hand.

821
01:09:44,514 --> 01:09:45,973
(BOTH LAUGHING)

822
01:09:50,019 --> 01:09:51,270
MICHAEL: Dance!

823
01:11:34,791 --> 01:11:36,249
(MICHAEL CLAPPING)

824
01:11:45,760 --> 01:11:46,843
Dad!

825
01:11:48,596 --> 01:11:50,055
Go home, Son.

826
01:12:01,484 --> 01:12:02,859
(DOG BARKS)

827
01:12:08,574 --> 01:12:10,075
(DOORBELL RINGS)

828
01:12:12,745 --> 01:12:15,080
Is this a friend of yours, then?

829
01:12:20,044 --> 01:12:22,045
How much is it gonna cost?

830
01:12:22,130 --> 01:12:24,464
And a happy Christmas to you, too.

831
01:12:26,551 --> 01:12:29,594
Not as much as you might think.
Maybe two grand.

832
01:12:29,804 --> 01:12:32,931
-But there's a good chance the council's...
-Two grand?

833
01:12:33,016 --> 01:12:34,850
I was talking about the auditions.

834
01:12:35,226 --> 01:12:37,519
Look, it's just a matter of the trip to London.

835
01:12:37,603 --> 01:12:39,646
I'll give you the money for the fare.

836
01:12:39,731 --> 01:12:41,773
I didn't come here to be patronized.

837
01:12:41,858 --> 01:12:46,236
Oh, no one's trying to patronize you.
You're being ridiculous.

838
01:12:46,320 --> 01:12:48,155
-Am I?
-Yes!

839
01:12:50,283 --> 01:12:51,783
(SIGHS)

840
01:12:52,994 --> 01:12:55,704
Thanks for everything you've done for Billy.

841
01:12:55,788 --> 01:12:57,831
But he is my son, isn't he?

842
01:12:58,458 --> 01:13:00,959
I'll handle this myself.

843
01:13:06,966 --> 01:13:09,301
(FLOORBOARDS CREAK)

844
01:13:51,677 --> 01:13:52,969
FOREMAN: Hey, fellow. Name. You.

845
01:13:53,054 --> 01:13:54,054
MAN 1: Paul.

846
01:13:54,138 --> 01:13:55,138
FOREMAN: Surname.

847
01:13:55,223 --> 01:13:56,890
-MAN 1: Felton.
-Felton.

848
01:13:58,309 --> 01:13:59,643
Shorty. You.

849
01:14:02,188 --> 01:14:03,563
-What? Thorpe.
-MAN 2: Thorpe.

850
01:14:06,192 --> 01:14:07,734
-Smith.
-FOREMAN: Smith.

851
01:14:07,819 --> 01:14:09,152
-MAN 3: Glenton.
-Glenton.

852
01:14:09,695 --> 01:14:10,862
-Kerner.
-Kerner.

853
01:14:11,906 --> 01:14:13,824
Is that the lot, then?

854
01:14:13,908 --> 01:14:17,702
MAN 4: Fucking hell.
I never thought I'd see you down here.

855
01:14:17,787 --> 01:14:19,454
Things change.

856
01:14:21,207 --> 01:14:22,833
FOREMAN: Right, you, name.

857
01:14:24,710 --> 01:14:26,169
Jackie Elliot.

858
01:14:26,254 --> 01:14:29,214
Well, glad to see you've come to your senses.

859
01:14:30,550 --> 01:14:32,509
Who's a big man now?

860
01:14:40,810 --> 01:14:42,310
(SIGHS)

861
01:14:43,563 --> 01:14:45,188
(BUS ENGINE STARTS)

862
01:14:45,273 --> 01:14:50,110
FOREMAN: Right. Okay, you lot. Over here.
All aboard the skylark. Look lively.

863
01:14:54,240 --> 01:14:57,492
Can't smoke on here, mate.
These are private buses.

864
01:15:06,210 --> 01:15:09,963
ALL: Scab! Scab! Scab! Scab! Scab! Scab!

865
01:15:10,047 --> 01:15:11,548
(BUS HORN HONKING)

866
01:15:35,364 --> 01:15:36,698
OFFICER: Keep back!

867
01:15:44,957 --> 01:15:49,252
Scab! Scab! Scab! Scab! Scab! Scab...

868
01:15:58,095 --> 01:15:59,763
TONY: Fuck off!

869
01:16:03,309 --> 01:16:05,727
Dad! Dad!

870
01:16:34,840 --> 01:16:36,383
Give us a hand.

871
01:16:56,570 --> 01:16:57,654
Dad!

872
01:16:58,739 --> 01:17:00,365
What the fuck are you doing?

873
01:17:09,125 --> 01:17:11,293
Dad, you can't go back! Not now!

874
01:17:11,377 --> 01:17:14,254
Look at the state of us, man.
What we got to offer the poor sod?

875
01:17:14,338 --> 01:17:15,880
You can't do this! Not now!

876
01:17:15,965 --> 01:17:18,258
Not after all this time!
Not after everything we've been through!

877
01:17:18,342 --> 01:17:22,262
It's for wee Billy!
He may be a fucking genius for all we know!

878
01:17:22,346 --> 01:17:24,639
For fuck's sake, Dad! You can't do this, man!

879
01:17:24,724 --> 01:17:26,599
Dad! Dad!

880
01:17:26,684 --> 01:17:28,059
MAN: Tony!

881
01:17:28,144 --> 01:17:31,396
He's only 11, for fuck's sake. He's a kid.

882
01:17:32,231 --> 01:17:33,690
He's just a fucking little kid.

883
01:17:33,774 --> 01:17:35,942
JACKIE: (CRYING) I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

884
01:17:36,027 --> 01:17:38,945
Please. Please.

885
01:17:39,030 --> 01:17:41,072
I'm sorry, Son.

886
01:17:43,451 --> 01:17:45,327
We're finished, Son.

887
01:17:47,121 --> 01:17:49,414
What choice have we got?

888
01:17:49,498 --> 01:17:51,875
Let's give the boy a fucking chance!

889
01:17:51,959 --> 01:17:56,004
Please. Please, don't do this to me.
Dad, we'll find him some money.

890
01:17:56,088 --> 01:17:58,089
We'll find it for him.

891
01:17:59,300 --> 01:18:01,259
MAN 1: What the fuck is he doing, Tony?

892
01:18:01,761 --> 01:18:04,387
It's okay. He's gonna be okay.

893
01:18:04,472 --> 01:18:06,639
MAN 2: Just get him out of here, Tony.

894
01:18:07,266 --> 01:18:09,809
MAN 3: Away. Leave it. Go on. Leave it.

895
01:18:09,894 --> 01:18:11,770
TONY: Let's go home, Dad.

896
01:18:16,192 --> 01:18:17,692
Dad's right, you know.

897
01:18:21,530 --> 01:18:23,323
Mom would've let you.

898
01:18:33,042 --> 01:18:35,377
GEORGE: All them 50 pences.

899
01:18:35,461 --> 01:18:39,089
Here. It was a toss-up between
a new punch bag or you.

900
01:18:39,173 --> 01:18:41,132
It's not even enough
for the bed and breakfast, man.

901
01:18:41,217 --> 01:18:43,259
Forget about it. You're dreaming.
Look at youse.

902
01:18:43,344 --> 01:18:46,054
Fucking scrabbling round for 50 pences.

903
01:18:46,347 --> 01:18:48,014
You've got to do better than that.

904
01:18:48,099 --> 01:18:50,683
GEORGE:
How! I'm gonna have a raffle at the welfare.

905
01:18:50,976 --> 01:18:53,269
And I'm gonna organize a concert.

906
01:18:53,354 --> 01:18:54,896
Thanks, George.

907
01:18:59,485 --> 01:19:03,822
TONY: Sheila's not got that kind of money.
She can't even keep the soup kitchen open.

908
01:19:03,906 --> 01:19:05,490
BILLY: George said we can
have another whip-round.

909
01:19:05,574 --> 01:19:08,993
TONY: Billy, there's no money left.
Get that through your head, man!

910
01:19:09,829 --> 01:19:12,997
GEORGE: The lads will always
dip into their buckets if we ask them.

911
01:19:13,082 --> 01:19:18,586
TONY: George, you know there's nothing left.
Stop putting ideas in his head, man!

912
01:19:19,422 --> 01:19:21,131
(JACKIE SNIFFLES)

913
01:19:22,675 --> 01:19:25,760
MAN: Come on, lads. Dig deep for the miners.

914
01:19:58,669 --> 01:20:02,547
Is that absolutely necessary?
Walk normal, will you?

915
01:20:08,971 --> 01:20:10,972
So what's it like, like?

916
01:20:14,143 --> 01:20:15,768
What's what like?

917
01:20:17,271 --> 01:20:18,480
London.

918
01:20:21,942 --> 01:20:24,944
I don't know, son.
I never made it past Durham.

919
01:20:26,739 --> 01:20:29,449
Have you never been, like?

920
01:20:29,533 --> 01:20:31,159
Why would I want to go to London?

921
01:20:31,243 --> 01:20:33,119
It's the capital city.

922
01:20:37,666 --> 01:20:39,501
Well, there's no mines in London.

923
01:20:39,585 --> 01:20:43,421
Christ. Is that all you think about?

924
01:21:08,405 --> 01:21:10,657
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING ON PIANO)

925
01:21:12,451 --> 01:21:14,369
WOMAN: Can I help you?

926
01:21:14,453 --> 01:21:17,539
JACKIE: Billy Elliot.
We've come for an audition.

927
01:21:18,582 --> 01:21:20,375
WOMAN: You mean William Elliot?

928
01:21:20,459 --> 01:21:21,626
JACKIE: Yeah, William.

929
01:21:21,710 --> 01:21:23,920
WOMAN: Yes. Can you go upstairs, please?

930
01:21:24,004 --> 01:21:26,005
-This way?
-Yes.

931
01:21:26,090 --> 01:21:27,298
Thanks.

932
01:21:57,538 --> 01:21:59,789
BOY 1: This your first time?
BOY 2: Yeah.

933
01:21:59,873 --> 01:22:02,542
I've been doing this for two years now.

934
01:22:03,502 --> 01:22:05,295
Hello.

935
01:22:05,754 --> 01:22:07,672
Nerve-racking, isn't it?

936
01:22:09,174 --> 01:22:10,883
Where are you from?

937
01:22:11,677 --> 01:22:13,678
Everington, County Durham.

938
01:22:14,179 --> 01:22:17,557
Durham? Isn't there an amazing cathedral?

939
01:22:19,268 --> 01:22:21,394
Don't know. Never been.

940
01:22:25,566 --> 01:22:27,692
DOCTOR: Up on the box, please.

941
01:22:29,028 --> 01:22:31,696
All right, bend over. Right down.

942
01:22:32,323 --> 01:22:35,617
And come up. And up.

943
01:22:35,701 --> 01:22:37,035
Head down.

944
01:22:37,745 --> 01:22:40,246
Tiny curvature here. Head down!

945
01:22:40,331 --> 01:22:41,497
How tiny?

946
01:22:41,582 --> 01:22:44,542
Might not be a problem. Come on.
Keep going.

947
01:22:45,753 --> 01:22:48,296
Right. All right. Jump up, William.

948
01:22:48,380 --> 01:22:50,757
It's Billy. Billy Elliot.

949
01:22:54,303 --> 01:22:58,222
Two, three, and four.

950
01:22:59,933 --> 01:23:01,100
Dad.

951
01:23:01,810 --> 01:23:04,395
Dad! Dad, for fuck's sake!

952
01:23:07,941 --> 01:23:09,108
I changed me mind.

953
01:23:09,193 --> 01:23:12,070
Get back in there! Don't be so stupid!

954
01:23:24,291 --> 01:23:25,541
(DOOR CLOSING)

955
01:23:27,044 --> 01:23:28,670
And you are?

956
01:23:29,755 --> 01:23:31,631
Billy Elliot from Everington.

957
01:23:31,715 --> 01:23:33,091
MAN: I beg your pardon?

958
01:23:33,175 --> 01:23:34,801
Billy Elliot.

959
01:23:35,094 --> 01:23:39,722
Yes, of course. Come to the bar, please, Billy.

960
01:23:47,856 --> 01:23:51,609
Left arm on the bar. Feet first.

961
01:23:52,569 --> 01:23:54,445
Arms second.

962
01:23:55,572 --> 01:23:59,909
Demi-plié, and hold.

963
01:24:04,915 --> 01:24:07,041
(ALL WHISPERING)

964
01:24:27,813 --> 01:24:31,399
Now, Billy,
we'd like to see you move to some music.

965
01:24:31,483 --> 01:24:33,651
Do you have a piece prepared?

966
01:24:33,736 --> 01:24:35,027
(BUTTON CLICKS)

967
01:24:35,487 --> 01:24:37,572
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

968
01:25:46,141 --> 01:25:47,642
(MUSIC STOPS)

969
01:25:58,821 --> 01:25:59,987
MAN: Thank you.

970
01:26:11,834 --> 01:26:15,169
You all right? What's the matter?

971
01:26:15,254 --> 01:26:17,588
It was a waste of fucking time!

972
01:26:19,633 --> 01:26:22,677
Don't be upset. It's only a stupid audition.

973
01:26:23,136 --> 01:26:25,513
-It's all right.
-Fuck off!

974
01:26:28,642 --> 01:26:30,017
There's always next year.

975
01:26:30,102 --> 01:26:32,270
Look, fuck off, will you!

976
01:26:33,355 --> 01:26:35,815
You bent bastard!

977
01:26:35,899 --> 01:26:37,108
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

978
01:26:40,487 --> 01:26:43,030
What on earth is going on here?

979
01:26:49,538 --> 01:26:51,581
How did it go?

980
01:26:56,128 --> 01:26:57,253
Shit!

981
01:26:59,506 --> 01:27:03,551
MAN: Mr Elliot, I'm afraid
that mutual respect and self-discipline

982
01:27:03,635 --> 01:27:07,471
are absolute prerequisites
for any pupil in this school.

983
01:27:07,556 --> 01:27:12,226
Such displays of violence cannot be
tolerated under any circumstances.

984
01:27:12,311 --> 01:27:13,978
Do you understand?

985
01:27:14,646 --> 01:27:17,398
I realize we shall have to
consider this very seriously,

986
01:27:17,482 --> 01:27:21,319
and it will be bound to
affect our final decision.

987
01:27:23,155 --> 01:27:28,159
Yes, well, just a few questions, then. Billy,

988
01:27:29,161 --> 01:27:33,831
can you tell us why you first became
interested in the ballet?

989
01:27:38,921 --> 01:27:40,296
Don't know.

990
01:27:44,009 --> 01:27:45,718
Just was.

991
01:27:46,845 --> 01:27:50,056
Well, was there any particular
aspect of the ballet

992
01:27:50,140 --> 01:27:53,309
which caught your imagination?

993
01:27:57,272 --> 01:27:59,231
The dancing.

994
01:27:59,858 --> 01:28:03,527
He dances all the time.
Every night after school.

995
01:28:03,612 --> 01:28:08,783
Yes. Well, we have a very enthusiastic letter
from Mrs Wilkinson,

996
01:28:08,867 --> 01:28:14,664
and she has told us of
your personal circumstances.

997
01:28:14,748 --> 01:28:18,960
Mr Elliot, are you a fan of the ballet?

998
01:28:21,129 --> 01:28:24,382
I wouldn't exactly say I was an expert.

999
01:28:26,885 --> 01:28:31,555
You do realize that all pupils
must attain the highest standards,

1000
01:28:31,640 --> 01:28:35,726
not just in ballet,
but in their ordinary academic work.

1001
01:28:35,811 --> 01:28:40,481
No child can succeed
without the 100% support of the family.

1002
01:28:41,900 --> 01:28:45,528
You are completely behind Billy.

1003
01:28:47,698 --> 01:28:48,864
Are you not?

1004
01:28:50,534 --> 01:28:53,911
Yes. Yes, of course.

1005
01:28:55,956 --> 01:28:58,499
Do you want to ask us any questions?

1006
01:29:03,588 --> 01:29:05,089
(JACKIE CLEARS THROAT)

1007
01:29:09,428 --> 01:29:11,554
No, not really. No.

1008
01:29:13,598 --> 01:29:15,266
MAN: Well, in that case,

1009
01:29:15,600 --> 01:29:18,519
we shall let you know in due course.

1010
01:29:24,860 --> 01:29:26,444
WOMAN: Just one last question.

1011
01:29:26,528 --> 01:29:28,279
Can I ask you, Billy,

1012
01:29:28,613 --> 01:29:32,658
what does it feel like when you're dancing?

1013
01:29:40,333 --> 01:29:41,709
Don't know.

1014
01:29:46,298 --> 01:29:47,798
Sort of feels good.

1015
01:29:50,052 --> 01:29:54,138
It's sort of stiff and that,
but once I get going,

1016
01:29:54,222 --> 01:29:56,557
then I forget everything.

1017
01:29:58,060 --> 01:29:59,226
And,

1018
01:30:03,315 --> 01:30:04,815
sort of disappear.

1019
01:30:08,403 --> 01:30:10,071
Sort of disappear.

1020
01:30:11,281 --> 01:30:13,908
Like I feel a change in me whole body.

1021
01:30:15,744 --> 01:30:17,912
Like there's fire in me body.

1022
01:30:19,456 --> 01:30:22,374
I'm just there, flying.

1023
01:30:25,003 --> 01:30:26,378
Like a bird.

1024
01:30:28,507 --> 01:30:30,174
Like electricity.

1025
01:30:36,765 --> 01:30:37,848
Yeah.

1026
01:30:40,185 --> 01:30:41,852
Like electricity.

1027
01:30:44,523 --> 01:30:46,524
Have a safe journey home.

1028
01:30:52,280 --> 01:30:53,656
Mr Elliot,

1029
01:30:54,116 --> 01:30:56,617
good luck with the strike.

1030
01:31:08,880 --> 01:31:10,047
GRANDMA: Toast!

1031
01:31:12,300 --> 01:31:14,718
I think you should get yourself a trade, son.

1032
01:31:17,889 --> 01:31:19,140
Something useful.

1033
01:31:23,854 --> 01:31:26,564
I could have been a professional dancer.

1034
01:31:30,735 --> 01:31:32,820
What happened to the dinosaurs, Miss?

1035
01:31:32,904 --> 01:31:34,738
TEACHER: They were crushed as well,

1036
01:31:34,823 --> 01:31:40,578
and the pressure of all of this caused
the plants and trees to change into coal.

1037
01:31:40,787 --> 01:31:42,705
-Ow!
-That's what must have happened to her.

1038
01:31:42,789 --> 01:31:45,583
Michael Caffrey,
if you have got something to say,

1039
01:31:45,667 --> 01:31:47,376
you can say it to the class.

1040
01:31:47,460 --> 01:31:48,544
Sorry, Miss.

1041
01:31:48,628 --> 01:31:53,716
TEACHER: So, gradually,
over hundreds of thousands of years...

1042
01:32:02,184 --> 01:32:03,601
Post!

1043
